{"desi_lesson":{"title":"Lesson 1: Basic Verbs: To Be & Common Actions","target_language":"Telugu","theme":"Basic Verbs: To Be & Common Actions","vocabulary":[{"english":"to be (I am)","target_language_script":"నేను ఉన్నాను","transliteration":"nenu unnaanu","pronunciation":"nay-noo un-naa-noo"},{"english":"to be (you are)","target_language_script":"మీరు ఉన్నారు","transliteration":"meeru unnaaru","pronunciation":"mee-roo un-naa-roo"},{"english":"to be (he/she/it is)","target_language_script":"అతను/ఆమె/అది ఉంది","transliteration":"atanu/aame/adi undi","pronunciation":"a-ta-noo/aa-may/a-dee un-dee"},{"english":"to eat","target_language_script":"తినండి","transliteration":"tinandi","pronunciation":"tin-an-dee"},{"english":"to drink","target_language_script":"తాగండి","transliteration":"taagandi","pronunciation":"taa-gan-dee"},{"english":"to sleep","target_language_script":"పడుకోండి","transliteration":"padukoondi","pronunciation":"pa-du-koon-dee"},{"english":"to work","target_language_script":"పని చేయండి","transliteration":"pani cheyandi","pronunciation":"pa-nee che-yan-dee"},{"english":"to go","target_language_script":"వెళ్ళండి","transliteration":"vellandi","pronunciation":"vel-lan-dee"},{"english":"to come","target_language_script":"రండి","transliteration":"randi","pronunciation":"ran-dee"},{"english":"to see","target_language_script":"చూడండి","transliteration":"choodandi","pronunciation":"choo-dan-dee"}],"example_sentences":[{"english":"I am happy.","target_language_script":"నేను సంతోషంగా ఉన్నాను.","transliteration":"nenu santhoshamgaa unnaanu.","pronunciation":"nay-noo san-toh-sham-gaa un-naa-noo"},{"english":"You are eating.","target_language_script":"మీరు తింటున్నారు.","transliteration":"meeru tintunnaaru.","pronunciation":"mee-roo tin-tun-naa-roo"},{"english":"He is sleeping.","target_language_script":"అతను పడుకుంటున్నాడు.","transliteration":"atanu padukuntunnaadu.","pronunciation":"a-ta-noo pa-du-kun-tun-naa-du"},{"english":"She is going to work.","target_language_script":"ఆమె పనికి వెళుతుంది.","transliteration":"aame paniki veluthundi.","pronunciation":"aa-may pa-nee-kee vel-u-tun-dee"},{"english":"It is coming.","target_language_script":"అది వస్తుంది.","transliteration":"adi vastundi.","pronunciation":"a-dee vas-tun-dee"}],"short_story":{"title":"A Busy Day","dialogue":[{"speaker":"Person A","target_language_script":"నేను ఉదయం పనికి వెళ్తున్నాను.","transliteration":"nenu udhayam paniki velthunnanu.","english":"I am going to work in the morning."},{"speaker":"Person B","target_language_script":"మీరు ఏమి తింటున్నారు?","transliteration":"meeru emi tintunnaaru?","english":"What are you eating?"},{"speaker":"Person A","target_language_script":"నేను అల్పాహారం తింటున్నాను.","transliteration":"nenu alpaharaam tintunnaanu.","english":"I am eating breakfast."}]},"quiz":[{"question":"How do you say 'I am eating' in Telugu?","options":["nenu tintunnaanu","meeru tintunnaaru","atanu tintunnaadu"],"answer":"nenu tintunnaanu"},{"question":"How do you say 'He is sleeping' in Telugu?","options":["atanu padukuntunnaadu","aame padukuntundi","nenu padukuntunnaanu"],"answer":"atanu padukuntunnaadu"},{"question":"How do you say 'to go' in Telugu?","options":["randi","vellandi","tinandi"],"answer":"vellandi"},{"question":"How do you say 'to drink' in Telugu?","options":["taagandi","padukoondi","cheyandi"],"answer":"taagandi"}]}}